<bug>
    <id>359559</id>
    <title>Firefox thinks webpage is "application/octet-stream," wants to save it</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1) Gecko/20061010 Firefox/2.0
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1) Gecko/20061010 Firefox/2.0</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">I just downloaded Firefox 2.0 yesterday, onto the new PC I also acquired yesterday.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">When browsing Wikipedia (logged-in), I clicked "Watchlist," and up popped a message saying that "Special-Watchlist" was an "application/octet-stream" and prompting me to save it.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">I clicked out of that, clicked Watchlist again, and this time it worked.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">A few minutes later, I clicked the Wikipedia logo to go to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page...same thing happened.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">This has happened four times in the last 15 minutes or so just clicking around Wikipedia (mainly to the main page and watchlist while trying to replicate this just now.).</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.6">This never happened on Wikipedia before in the past year-plus of browsing it with Firefox 1.X on my old computer.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Sometimes</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">See above.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">As I said, though, I had to click around a while to replicate what I suddenly noticed the first time it happened.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">OS is "Windows XP Media Center Edition 2005," according to a sticker on it.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
